cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.SY

The paper discusses the use of deep learning in computer vision, speech recognition, and natural language processing, which are all subfields of computer science that fall under the arXiv categories of cs.AR (Hardware Architecture), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the use of FPGAs as an alternative to GPUs for hardware acceleration, which falls under the arXiv category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses the use of high-level software practices in the deep learning community, which falls under the arXiv category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
